Program: The Documentary
Title: Her Story Made History: Vigdis Finnbogadottir
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswg28
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 22 Feb 2018
In 1980, the tiny country of Iceland did something no other nation had done. They elected a female head of state. BBC chief international correspondent Lyse Doucet travels to Reykjavik to meet Vigdis Finnbogadottir. Now 87, she was president for exactly 16 years and remains the longest-serving elected female head of state of any country to date. "That’s what I have given to the girls of this country," she says: “If she can, I can.” (Photo: Vigdis Finnbogadottir) Show less